That's because the mascot image is being positioned too high inside the container.

Looking at your screenshot, the mascot's **head is clipped by the top edge** of the green container. You need to move the image **down**, not up.

Try this:

```css
.right-illustration {
    position: relative;
    width: 600px;
    height: 804px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-top-left-radius: 40px;
}

.mascot {
    position: absolute;
    width: 700px;

    right: -130px;

    /* move DOWN */
    top: 80px;

    z-index: 2;
}
```

Or if you're currently using `bottom`:

```css
.mascot {
    position: absolute;
    width: 700px;
    right: -130px;

    /* less negative = lower image */
    bottom: -20px;
}
```

