### What Figma actually shows

The mascot should look approximately like:

```text
 -------------------------
|                         |
|        HEAD             |
|                         |
|       TORSO             |
|                         |
|      HANDS              |
|                         |
|       KNEES             |
 -------------------------
```

Not:

```text
 -------------------------
|       HEAD CUT          |
|                         |
|       TORSO             |
|                         |
|                         |
|       FEET              |
 -------------------------
```

If you want the exact Figma proportions from your screenshot, use:

```css
.mascot {
    position: absolute;
    width: 760px;
    right: -170px;
    top: 35px;
}
```

This typically shows the full head and cuts around the knees, which is very close to the design you've been showing.
